  <mads:note type="source">Brill's New Pauly: "Earlier thought to be a writer of comedies 
    because of a transcription error in Ath. 15,668c, where three lines are quoted 
    from Κάλλιπος ἐν Παννυχίδι (‘C. in the Pannychís). Since the appearance 
    of the PBerolinensis 13417 with the rest of the drinking poem Pannychís 
    by Callimachus [3], including the lines quoted by Athenaeus, 
    there can be no doubt that the phrase in question should read Καλλίμαχος...
    "Hidber, Thomas (Bern). "Callipus." Brill's New Pauly. Antiquity 
    volumes edited by: Hubert Cancik and Helmuth Schneider . Brill, 2009.
    Brill Online. Tufts University Library. 02 September 2009</mads:note>   
